{
  "texts": [
    "This technique involves appending natural language texts to either the beginning or the end of inputs or outputs.",
    "It aims to guide the pre-trained models towards executing particular functions [95], [96].",
    "Among the various fine-tuning methods, prompt tuning stands out for a variety of benefits, which make them particularly suitable for FL for which computational efficiency and task effectiveness are paramount.A key significant advantage of prompt tuning is that it often does not require modifications to the FM parameters, thereby markedly lowering computational overhead.",
    "Furthermore, in scenarios involving limited training data, skillfully crafted prompts can effectively substitute for hundreds of labeled examples [97], demonstrating its potential to enhance model performance with minimal resources.",
    "Prompt tuning specifically focuses on optimizing the likelihood of obtaining a desired output by augmenting the original input with trainable embedded prompts."
  ]
}